<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kenneth R. Weiss 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PLAY BALL: When those words open the baseball season today, fans across 
Ventura County will be rooting for hometown players who made the big leagues. 
Terry Pendleton, for one, has a loyal following in Oxnard, where he started in 
Little League at Colonia Park. . . . On occasion Pendleton returns to Channel 
Islands High School to inspire young ballplayers, said Don Cardinal, his former 
coach who recently retired. "He comes back and signs their hats and gloves and 
they really love that." 
</P>
<P>
 ALL ABOARD: The first Metrolink train pulls out of Oxnard at 5:31 this 
morning, aimed at helping relieve traffic congestion on quake-damaged freeways 
(B5). . . . In grand tradition, Oxnard leaders plan a big send-off before they 
hop the train to Moorpark and then take a shuttle bus back. Bill Davis, the 
county's Metrolink representative, warns of mistakes made by Camarillo 
politicians. "When the train stopped, I said, 'C'mon guys, let's get off the 
train.' They just kept yakking." And they missed their stop. 
</P>
<P>
 CYBER SURFING: Beginning this morning, Ventura County library patrons can take 
the information superhighway to get books from libraries as far north as Paso 
Robles. County librarians are joining a computer network that allows patrons to 
search library shelves in Santa Barbara and San Luis Obispo counties and borrow 
any of their 1.1 million books. . . . Within six months, terminals at the 14 
operating branches will be able to search some data bases on the Internet. 
</P>
<P>
 BATTERY CHANGE: So you've either changed your clocks to daylight-savings time 
or you're an hour late for work. Never mind that for now. County fire officials 
have another chore for you: Change your smoke alarm batteries. . . . They say 
75% of homes have a smoke detector, but half of those don't work because of an 
old or missing battery. The "Change Your Clock, Change Your Batteries" program 
is brought to you by the Assn. of Fire Chiefs, the American Burn Assn. and the 
ever-helpful Eveready Battery Co. Major Leaguers 
</P>
<P>
 Baseball players from Ventura County: 
</P>
<P>
 Terry Pendleton (Oxnard): Braves 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Tackett (Oxnard): Orioles 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Radinsky (Simi Valley): White Sox 
</P>
<P>
 Bobby Ayala (Oxnard): Mariners 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Gross (Fillmore): Dodgers 
</P>
<P>
 Bret Saberhagen (Thousand Oaks): Mets 
</P>
</TEXT>
