<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOMELESS BEGGAR SAVES 2 TRAPPED IN FIERY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A homeless man who was begging for quarters plunged twice into a burning car 
to rescue the two people trapped inside. 
</P>
<P>
 "It wasn't no big deal," Michael Dennis said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was just the right thing. I saw two old people burning up. You can't just 
ignore that." 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis was begging Saturday afternoon when a car driven by Margaret Waltzer, 
67, struck a truck and a traffic signal pole and caught fire. 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis rescued her and her 79-year-old husband, Elmo. 
</P>
<P>
 They were in stable condition at Baptist-Mercy Medical Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
