<P>
 In your editorial of March 28 you ask, "Is it reasonable to establish a set of 
ethical expectations for our politicians that rises along with their 
prominence, thus setting up a situation in which the bombshell explodes only at 
the point at which it is most damaging to the country?" My answer as a citizen 
voter uncommitted politically is a resounding yes! It is not only reasonable 
but essential to have leaders of moral fiber. Not considering here the issue of 
having to trust them nor the effect of leadership role models on the rest of 
us, to tolerate and accept less from national leaders is a sure route to the 
disruption caused by certain exposure of their wrongdoing. I, as a citizen of 
