<P>
 The Simi Valley Youth Employment Service is seeking businesses willing to 
participate in its eighth annual job fair. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair, scheduled May 7, is intended to help 16- to 22-year-olds find jobs 
and learn about careers, coordinator Sandra Thompson said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Young people get a chance to ask questions and learn about different 
possibilities, and employers get a chance to do some hiring," she said. "It 
works out well for everyone." 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, about 50 employers and 1,000 youths attended the fair, Thompson 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Employers range from retail clothing and fast-food chains to large 
corporations and government agencies. 
</P>
