<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; YOUTHS' DISPUTE LEADS TO GUNFIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A verbal dispute between two groups of teen-agers escalated into gunfire early 
Easter Sunday as two of the youths were driving away from the scene, 
investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two 17-year-olds from Thousand Oaks were driving west on Lynn Road at Avenida 
de las Floras about 3 a.m. Sunday when they heard between one and four shots 
fired at them from behind, sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 A bullet pierced their car, passed through a headrest and grazed the scalp of 
one of the boys, deputies said. The youth, whose name was not released because 
of his age, was treated at Los Robles Regional Medical Center and released, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said a dispute between the pair and another group of four or 
five juveniles provoked the shooting. All are believed to be involved in gangs, 
according to deputies. 
</P>
<P>
 Police are looking for the suspects, who fled west on Lynn Road in a black 
car, authorities said. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
