<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SOUTH COUNTY; DRIVING SKILLS CLASSES FOR SENIORS OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A series of two-day classes for senior citizens who want to improve their 
driving skills and earn automobile insurance discounts will start April 11 in 
Mission Viejo and San Clemente and continue throughout the month. 
</P>
<P>
 Sponsored by the American Assn. of Retired Persons, the workshops include 
eight hours of classroom instruction.Following graduation, participants are 
given a state Department of Motor Vehicles certificate qualifying them for 
insurance discounts. 
</P>
<P>
 Cost for the program is $8. Preregistration is required and must be done at 
the facility where the classes are being held. 
</P>
<P>
 Classes in April will be held: 
</P>
<P>
 * April 11-12 at the Norman P. Murray Community and Senior Center, 24932 Oso 
Viejo, Mission Viejo, from 8 a.m. to noon. For more information, call (714) 
348-2063. 
</P>
<P>
 * April 11-12 at the San Clemente Senior Center, 242 Avenida del Mar, from 
9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. For more information, call (714) 498-3322. 
</P>
<P>
 * April 16 and 23 at the Laguna Beach Senior Center at Lang Park, 384 Legion 
St., from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. For more information, call (714) 497-2441. 
</P>
<P>
 * April 18-19 at Glendale Federal Bank, 24221 Calle de la Louisa, Laguna 
Hills, from 8:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. For more information, call (714) 768-7771. 
</P>
<P>
 * April 20 and 27 at the Dana Point Parks and Recreation Services office, 
34052 Del Obispo St., from 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. For more information, call (714) 
496-4251. 
</P>
<P>
 * April 23 and 30 at the Freedom Village Retirement Community, 23442 El Toro 
Road, Lake Forest, from 12:30 to 4:30 p.m. For more information, call (714) 
472-4700. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
