<SECTION>
<P>
Business; Part D; Page 1; Column 1; Financial Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
98 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: THIS COULD BE A MEATY STORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Christian publishing company hopes there's more to know about Dave Thomas 
than his love for hamburgers and spicy chicken sandwiches. 
</P>
<P>
 The founder of Wendy's Old Fashioned Hamburgers has signed a contract with the 
Zondervan Corp. for a "personal success book, showing the average person how to 
improve his life by applying the same simple principles that turned Wendy's 
into a successful worldwide business," Zondervan said. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas will explain his philosophy of life and his Christian beliefs in the 
book. Scheduled for an August release, it is tentatively titled "Well Done." 
</P>
</TEXT>
