<P>
 State's Exports Up Only 2% in 1993: State commerce officials said the slight 
increase was because of a huge decline in aircraft and aerospace products and a 
slump in European markets.The export of transportation equipment, which 
includes aircraft and aerospace items, fell 28.7%. If that is not included, 
state exports grew by 8.4%. Total worldwide exports of California goods were 
$70.3 billion. That total does not include legal and financial services, 
construction, movies, recordings, software and foreign tourism, which would 
increase the figure by $30 billion. 
</P>
