3.4 EARTHQUAKE RATTLES PALM SPRINGS AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 3.4-magnitude earthquake shook the desert about 30 miles southwest of Palm 
Springs on Sunday evening, Caltech seismologists said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 8:25 p.m. temblor was not an aftershock of either the Northridge or Big 
Bear earthquakes, according to Caltech seismologist Kathy Willis. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no reports of injuries or damage. 
</P>
