<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL / DAILY REPORT; NCAA WOMEN; SUB-REGIONALS ADDED FOR NEXT 
SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After expanding to 64 teams this year, the NCAA women's basketball tournament 
will undergo additional change in 1995.The tournament will be divided into 16 
sub-regionals to be played on the courts of the top 16 seeded teams. 
</P>
<P>
 Two first-round games will be played at each of the 16 sites, followed by a 
single second-round game. The winners will advance to the regional semifinals, 
whose sites already have been determined. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Leslie, a 6-foot-5 senior from USC, received another player-of-the-year 
award, this one from the U.S. Basketball Writers Assn. Ceal Barry of Colorado 
was selected coach of the year and Purdue's Leslie Johnson was chosen freshman 
of the year. 
</P>
