</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALICIA DI RADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Are you among the 75,000 people who have attended Golden West College? If so, 
the school is looking for you. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials are trying to locate at least 6,000 graduates to form the Golden 
West College Alumni Assn., spokeswoman Lori Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Golden West College Foundation is creating a database of names, addresses 
and phone numbers of former students, she said. Volunteers are also combing 
through old records to track down graduates. 
</P>
<P>
 Once officials create a network, they will invite graduates back to campus, 
where they can help the college offer an up-to-date education for current 
students, Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 "For community colleges to stay viable these days, they need more resources," 
Thomas said. "For example, they need input from alumni who have become police 
officers and can come back to tell criminal justice students about what is 
important in police work today." 
</P>
<P>
 Officials hope that former students can assist the college by raising money 
that would help the school keep up with technology. They also intend to start 
social activities such as picnics and reunions for graduates, Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 To register or volunteer, call (714) 895-8315.ALICIA DI RADO 
