<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; SEAT OPEN ON CITY TRAFFIC COMMISSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents interested in a position on the Traffic and Transportation 
Commission can pick up application forms at City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission is responsible for traffic and parking issues in the city, and 
there is one vacancy on the five-member municipal body, which meets the third 
Wednesday of every month in City Hall. 
</P>
<P>
 The open seat was recently vacated by Commissioner Patsy Wood. 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for filing the application is 5 p.m. April 15. The form must be 
returned to the city clerk's office.  
</P>
<P>
 Commissioners must be Mission Viejo residents and registered voters. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the opening, call (714) 348-2052. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
