<HEADLINE>
<P>
VEHICLE HITS POWER POLE, CAUSING OUTAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 18,000 homes were without electricity for several hours early Sunday 
after a driver fell asleep and struck a utility pole in Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 City crews restored power to all the homes by 7:35 a.m., Los Angeles 
Department of Water and Power spokeswoman Debra Sass said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's unusual to have that many customers lose power from one accident," Sass 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, who was not injured, crashed into the pole at the intersection of 
Ethel Avenue and Oxnard Street shortly after 1 a.m., after dozing off at the 
wheel, said Los Angeles Police Officer Vince Vicary. 
</P>
