<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 ARRESTED IN AUTO THEFT AFTER CHASE THROUGH 3 CITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two 15-year-olds and an adult were arrested Sunday on suspicion of auto theft 
and evading arrest after allegedly leading police on a 30-minute car chase that 
passed through three cities and reached speeds of 100 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the two juveniles and Jose M. Cortez, 18, all of Santa Ana, stole 
a car in Garden Grove and were later spotted in Orange by an Orange police 
officer. A chase began that lead police and California Highway Patrol along 
freeways and streets in Garden Grove, Orange and Anaheim, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The pursuit ended at Euclid Street and Hazard Avenue in Garden Grove, where 
the alleged thieves jumped out of the car. Police reported capturing the three 
as they tried to flee on foot. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a miracle there wasn't a major accident. These guys drove like utter 
maniacs," Orange Police Department Lt. Trey Sirks said. The two juveniles were 
sent to Juvenile Hall, and Cortez was being held at County Jail, Sirks said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
